of Conceit with them&s;elves upon it, as if
they carried the <HI>Devil</HI> on their Shoulders,
as the Cau&s;e of their Decripedne&s;s and
Incurvity. And &s;uch an Offence would be
of ill Con&s;equence.</P>
<P>Rea&s;onably then &s;peaking, there was
not much in the Di&s;ea&s;e and Cure of this
Woman. Excepting that Part, which <HI>Sa|tan</HI>
bears, in the Story, there is nothing
wonderful in it. And &s;uppo&s;ing <HI>Je&s;us</HI>
