rational, and cabali&s;tical Notion of
Hell, which I have learned of the Fa|thers,
who &s;ignify, that the babyloni&s;h
<PB N="42" REF="49">
and bewilder'd State of Chri&s;t's Church
may be call'd <HI>Hell,</HI> becau&s;e, as the
Word <GAP DESC="FOREIGN"> does import, it is a State <HI>with|out
Vi&s;ion.</HI> Hence <HI>Origen</HI> &s;ays,<NOTE N="34" PLACE="foot">Con&s;equens autem e&s;t ei, qui cogno&s;cit quae &s;it Hieru&s;alem in divi&s;ione verae Haeredita$is filio|rum I&s;rael, ut intelligat Sermonem de Gehenna. <HI>In Matt. Ch.</HI> xxiii.</NOTE> that
whoever can $orm to him&s;elf an <HI>Idea</HI> of
the Church in time to come, when &s;he
