which I am now to &s;peak to.</P>
<P><PB N="56" REF="63">
Tho' the Fathers, again&s;t who&s;e Autho|rity
I dare not write, or I &s;hould be tempt|ed
to it in this Ca&s;e, acknowledge the
Letter of this Story, &s;u&s;pecting only &s;ome
<NOTE N="53" PLACE="foot">Forta&s;&s;e verum non erat, <HI>Judaeos cum Sa|maritanis Commercium non habere,</HI>&mdash;ac ne illud quidem verum, <HI>neque Hau&s;torium habes, &amp; Pu|teus altus e&s;t,</HI>&mdash;forta&s;&s;e etiam neque illud, <HI>quod Jacob ex Puteo biberit, &amp; filii ejus, &amp; pecora</HI> ejus. <HI>Origen. in Loc.</HI></NOTE> particular Pa&s;&s;ages of it; yet they
